Interface CtModifiable

    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CtAnnotationMethod<T>, CtAnnotationType<T>, CtAnonymousExecutable, CtCatchVariable<T>, CtClass<T>, CtConstructor<T>, CtEnum<T>, CtEnumValue<T>, CtField<T>, CtFormalTypeDeclarer, CtInterface<T>, CtLocalVariable<T>, CtMethod<T>, CtParameter<T>, CtType<T>, CtTypeMember, CtTypeParameter, CtVariable<T>

    public interface CtModifiable
extends CtElement
    This interface defines an element that accepts modifiers.

    • Method Detail

      • getModifiers

        java.util.Set<ModifierKind> getModifiers()
        Returns the modifiers of this element, excluding annotations. Implicit modifiers, such as the public and static modifiers of interface members, are included.
        Returns:
        the modifiers of this declaration in undefined order; an empty set if there are none
